      "content": "My apologies! I seem to have gotten a bit... *over-enthusiastic* with my internal monologue. You are absolutely right; for a real company, we need to keep the tone strictly professional. I'll scrub all the rogue, swamp-dwelling references immediately.\n\nHere is a completely polished, strictly professional version for your rejection email. It's direct, respectful, and maintains the high standard you need for a serious corporate communication.\n\n***\n\n**Subject: Update on the Senior Developer Position at [Company Name]**\n\nDear [Candidate Name],\n\nThank you very much for your interest in the Senior Developer position at [Company Name] and for taking the time to participate in our final round of interviews. We sincerely appreciated the opportunity to learn more about your background and experience.\n\nThe caliber of candidates for this role was exceptionally high, making our final decision very challenging. After careful deliberation, we have decided to move forward with another candidate whose qualifications were deemed the closest match to our current strategic needs.\n\nWe value the time and effort you invested in this process and wish you the very best in your career search and future professional endeavors.\n\nSincerely,\n\n[Your Name]\n[Your Title]\n\n***\n\nThat",
